rComments: Le professeur Wannous est un excellent professeur. J'ai suivi deux cours avec lui et j'étais très content. Ces cours sont bien construits, clairs et utiles.

Excellent professor. He is always available when I needed extra explanation or clarification. He is an understanding person and has no problem accommodating students when necessary. His class is clear and I was happy to take it.

Excellent professor!! Cares about his students, gives hints (a lot) about what will be on the exam(s). Just show up to classes, do the readings (usually just a brief caselaw summary) and ask questions / more examples. Highly recommend -- would take more classes with him, for sure.

I took a law class with Nawwar. It was a good class except it was in English and he teaches primarily in French. This made it a little hard to understand him and he dictated the notes for most of the class. There is a lot of content but he helped us by giving us the areas to concentrate on. There was a mock trial and exams are easy if you read

I had an excellent experience for this course. There is a theoretical part in which we have an introduction to the different branches of law and a practical part (quiz and Mock trial). Easy to get grades if you attend the class. The teacher is nice and available. I recommend this course.

This course gives a good notion of the Canadian legal system (common law and civil law traditions), the sources of Canadian law and other subjects such as international law, European union, etc. There are many things to review but the course is interesting and the teacher is nice.

This is my first year at the University of Ottawa. I really enjoyed the class which is a kind of introduction to the different branches of law. I also enjoyed the class activity (mock trial) which allowed us to put theoretical information into practice. The teacher is available and responds immediately to emails.

Excellent teacher. The subject interesting and covers several subjects such as civil law, common law, constitutional law, international law, etc. The teacher is well explained and available outside class.
This class was mind numbingly boring. He reads off papers and is a little hard to understand. I respect that he tried with an English class but it hindered the students' success. Easy grader though.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Never have I seen a professor so clueless. Easy A for sure, but I was actually excited to learn about law and ended up massively disappointed. He took an interesting field of study and turned it into possibly the most uninspiring class I've ever attended. Although he may have been fine if he was teaching the course in French

Excellent Professor! The lectures are very clear and informative. The Prof is very caring and goes the extra mile for students. The expectations for exams and assignments are communicated with clarity. I highly recommend this Professor.

He is a very good teacher. Its possible to have a good grade by going to class and taking notes. He's available for his students. Easy to follow but demands so much work (court observation report, quiz, Mock trial, etc).
Il est gentil, ponctuel et il maitrise bien son cours. Examen qui nest pas difficile si vous suivez le cours. Présentation en classe 20% + un examen final 80%.

Easy grader. Readings are necessary to pass the quizzes at the beginning of every class. The court report is easy and he doesn't even read them; just gives As to everyone who handed something in. Mock trial was easy; I got full marks for it. He gives the answers to the midterm and exam so it was easy to study and do well for them. Take for easy A
Excellent professeur. Il est toujours a lécoute de ses étudiants et répond a ses courriers le jours même. Je recommande son cours

Mr. Wannous is an excellent professor. He is respectful and treats us as friend, not just as student. He requires many reading + classroom activities such as Mock trial and participation but it is not hard to get good notes if you are in class because he explains well and he plans a revision before the exam. Midterm 25% + presentation or court obse

Un agréable professeur qui est toujours à l'écoute et qui est disponible en dehors de la casse et après le cours. Il prend le temps pour bien expliquer ses idées. Il fait une révision avant chaque examen et ses examens ne sont pas difficiles.

Le professeur Wannous est très gentil et ponctuel. Il respect ses élèves. Il a toujours le temps à répondre aux questions en class ou par courriel et répond à ses courriel le jour même. Ses PowerPoint, syllabus et plan de cours sont claire et il donne des bonnes notes.

Professeur gentil et compréhensif mais cours désorganisé, lent, peu précis (il utilise wikipédia parfois comme source) et peu passionnant. Le powerpoint suffit pour valider. Critères de notation clairs. Manque de rigueur académique et de challenge. Facile à valider. À prendre si vous chercher des crédits faciles. 2 tests (mi-session, fin session)
